Output: `{"name":"Jane","age":30}` ✅

Here's the complete program (`Program.cs`):

```csharp
using System;
using System.Text.Json;

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions { PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase };
var json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(new Person("Jane", 30), options);
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string Name, int Age);
```

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase` — it converts PascalCase properties (`Name`, `Age`) to camelCase (`name`, `age`) during serialization. The project targets `net8.0` with just the default SDK, no extra packages needed.
